colnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"–1220":"–1220","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1165–Male":"1165–Deceased","1217":"1217","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"about 1217","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Maud","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Fulletby was born in Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of William de Fulleby. She married Sir William de Willoughby x in 1189, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1220, in Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"–1220":"–1220","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","1217":"1217","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"umbes 1217","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Horncastle, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–1220":"–1220","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1165–Male":"1165–Kuollut","1217":"1217","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"noin 1217","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England","Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Horncastle, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, , England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–1220":"–1220","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1210–1257":"1210–1257","1217–1257":"1217–1257","1165–Male":"1165–Décédé","1217":"1217","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1189":"1189","1210":"1210","1220":"1220","1165":"1165","1170":"1170","Abt 1217":"environ 1217","Willoughby, Lincolnshire, England":"Willoughby, Lincolnshire, Angleterre","Horncastle, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Horncastle, Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Of Wiloughby, Lincolnshire England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Roy